COREVAULT ENTERPRISE COMMERCIAL AND END-USER LICENSE AGREEMENT (EULA)
VERSION 1.0.0 — PRODUCTION BUILD (2026)

This document establishes a legally binding contract between the end-user (Individual or Corporate Entity) and CoreVault Security Operations regarding the application deployment.

1. PERSONAL WORKSPACE ALLOWANCE (NON-COMMERCIAL)
CoreVault grants a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to individual private citizens to execute the cryptographic binary solely for personal, non-commercial data sanitation and asset isolation.

2. CORPORATE, MEDICAL, AND GOVERNED AGENCY DEPLOYMENT RESTRICTION
Any deployment within a facility, medical center, healthcare network, financial institution, enterprise network, or government facility is strictly prohibited unless an official Master Enterprise Activation Token is bought and permanently validated on the network nodes.

3. COMPLIANCE AUDITING AND TAMPER CONTROL
Unauthorized commercial configurations executed without localized master cryptographic registration constitute an explicit breach of copyright law and international proprietary software protection treaties. CoreVault reserves the right to enforce localized node termination loops if systemic license validation failures are registered.